title: Grateful Dead Live at Richmond Coliseum on 1983-10-08
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, Minglewood Blues, Brown Eyed Women, Cassidy, West L.A. Fadeaway, Hell In A Bucket-> Deal

Set 2

Day Job-> Playin' In The Band-> Crazy Fingers-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Spoonful-> Wharf Rat-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
I like it This recording is very good. In all the years they played this building which is 1983,84 and 85 seems everyone made good quality recordings. Maybe it was the perfect sounding building.
 As far as this recording I would of loved having this way back then. Lucky enough to have been all these tours from 82 threw 89 but never had time to make recordings to travel around with. Now I listen everyday and this is a keeper.
